subject: Re: My Progress
msgSnippet: I m a fellow learner of QS, and I feel I should offer my story, which seems very different from yours, so perhaps it may be enlightening: I began around the
messageBody:
I'm a fellow learner of QS, and I feel I should offer my story, which seems very different from yours, so perhaps it may be enlightening:

I began around the same time you did at the beginning of the Manual on Quikscript provided by Kingsley Read as the Bible on QS.  At first I learned the alphabet, which is merely Junior Quikscript.  Senior QS looked daunting at first, and early on I figured merely studying Junior would be enough.  But after I continued to read the Manual, which goes on to cover Senior QS, and once I started practicing writing in Senior, I realized that Junior was really just "baby talk" in comparison to Senior.  English comes out much more compacted (not to mention more beautiful) in the much more cursive Senior QS than it does in Junior.  I believe if you're going to take the time to learn the alphabet at all, you should move on to Senior afterwards.

And if you do that, you'll find yourself WRITING in cursive Quikscript, which is what K.R. really had in mind in creating QS, and you'll absorb it, I think, much faster than you would studying a gazillion individual English words spelled out in Junior, which seems to be what the Memrise course is providing.
